    "\"'• Integration with RLHF and symbolic reasoning.",
    "Reward-weighted loss in DRaFT-Q provides a natural foundation for integration with RLHF pipelines or symbolic execution environments where the reward function can be learned or dynamically inferred.• Application to multi-task and instruction-tuned datasets.",
    "DRaFT-Q can be extended to multi-task settings (e.g., FLAN, T0) where adapter rank could be routed based on task context or instruction structure.• Enhancing interpretability.",
    "The use of token-level weights and rank evolution can be visualized using heatmaps and rank-trace plots, aiding in better understanding model adaptation during training.• Hybrid adaptive methods.",
    "DRaFT-Q could be combined with other approaches such as DoRA, AdaLoRA, or curriculum learning to further optimize training stability, convergence speed, and parameter sharing."
